    <worksheet name='Sheet 5'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Do Personality Dimensions Predict Engagement Levels? — Average Engagement by MBTI Type</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>All eight types sit between 0.85 and 1.07, meaning average engagement is broadly comparable across personality types — but this is exactly what makes the line charts above it so important, because averages hide when and how spikes occur.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources>
            <datasource caption='eeg_timeseries_final_version_04' name='federated.0m07frz1lbw2je1as0pel1gpxlrf' />
