      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='16'>Does Personality Shape When and How Students Engage? - MBTI Dimensions and Neural Engagement Patterns</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>This dashboard examines whether the four MBTI personality dimensions, Energy (I/E), Mind (S/N), Nature (T/F), and Tactics (J/P), produce distinct neural engagement trajectories during formal presentations. Each line chart compares average engagement (β/α ratio) across 30-second time bins for the two personality types within each dimension. The grouped bar chart below summarises average engagement by type across the full session. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
